      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_CreateNationalGridWestLinkedServers",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to create a linked server in SQL Server. A linked server allows SQL Server to execute commands against OLE DB data sources on different servers. This specific procedure sets up a linked server named "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "KeyspanWestSpecialLedgerAccountBilling",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " using the Microsoft Jet OLE DB provider to access a data source located at a network path. The procedure is part of the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "NationalGridWest",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema within the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "OEC",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " database."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity of this stored procedure is low. It primarily involves a single call to the system stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "sp_addlinkedserver",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", which is used to define a new linked server. There are no complex logic, loops, or conditional statements involved."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
